Class SQLExpressionMatchFilter<T,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.jdbc.expr.SQLExpressionMatchFilter<T,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of target
    V - type of expression
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    BaseFilter<T>, BaseSQLFilter<T>, PatternFilter<T>, SQLFilter<T>, Targetted<T>

    public class SQLExpressionMatchFilter<T,V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements SQLFilter<T>, PatternFilter<T>
    A SQLFilter that compares two SQLExpressions. Note these do not include any filter required by the SQLExpression so factory methods are used to ensure these are in place.
